basic.description:
An overview of principles of physical fitness and wellness with an emphasis on the planning and implementation of a personalized physical fitness program.
NOTE    Not available to students in a KINE or PHED Plan.
NOTE    Also offered online. Consult Continuing and Distance Studies. Learning Hours may vary.
LEARNING HOURS    108 (36L;72P)
basic.subject: HLTH
basic.title: Physical Fitness and Wellness

extra.enrollment_requirement:
Not available to students in KINE or PHED plans.
Prerequisite    Level 2
One-Way Exclusion    May not be taken with or after: KNPE 227/3.0 (formerly PHED 155/3.0); KNPE 255/3.0 (formerly PHED 255/3.0).
